Explanation:
A server is a computer that provides services to other computers over a network.
The domain name foobar.com makes the website easier to access than typing an IP address.
The www record points www.foobar.com to the server IP address 8.8.8.8.
The web server, Nginx, handles HTTP/HTTPS requests from users.
The application server runs the application logic.
The application files are the code base of the website.
The database, MySQL, stores persistent data.
The server communicates with the user's computer using HTTP/HTTPS over TCP/IP.

Issues:
This infrastructure has a single point of failure because everything is on one server.
There can be downtime during maintenance or deployment because services may need to restart.
It cannot scale well because all traffic goes to one server.
